1ï¸âƒ£ What are EP and BVA? (1-Line Each)

Equivalence Partitioning (EP): Divide inputs into groups where the system behaves the same; test one value per group.

Boundary Value Analysis (BVA): Test edge values (min, max, just inside and outside boundaries) where defects commonly occur.

2ï¸âƒ£ When to Use EP & BVA

Use EP to reduce test cases.

Use BVA to catch edge-case defects.

Best practice: Apply EP first, then BVA.

